WEBVTT

00:00.033 --> 00:01.999
Lloyd, I have told you.

00:02.000 --> 00:03.767
It's all decided about Georgie.

00:03.768 --> 00:06.000
I'll be coming on my own! We...

00:11.434 --> 00:13.366
(SCREAMS, SOBS)

00:13.367 --> 00:14.800
Will you marry me?

00:14.801 --> 00:16.433
Yes, I will.

00:16.434 --> 00:17.400
Marvelous!

00:17.401 --> 00:19.899
Gino's eyes glow when
he talks of children.

00:19.900 --> 00:21.800
And there's a good chance
that I can't have them.

00:21.801 --> 00:23.932
The doctor told me after my miscarriage.

00:23.933 --> 00:26.466
We're flying the new
Kangaroo tourist class.

00:26.467 --> 00:28.299
Cairo overnight, Tripoli, and then Rome.

00:28.300 --> 00:29.099
- (SCREAMING)
- Push.

00:29.100 --> 00:30.932
REGINA: Flying Officer Gordon Walsh.

00:30.933 --> 00:32.500
Message reads,

00:32.500 --> 00:38.533
"For unto us a child is born
in a manger in Inverness."

00:38.534 --> 00:40.767
Have you thought of a name yet?

00:40.768 --> 00:41.767
SARAH: No.

00:41.768 --> 00:44.433
And he'll be Nordmann on
the birth certificate.

00:44.434 --> 00:46.566
Perhaps we should go our own ways.

00:46.567 --> 00:48.166
For all of Regina's shortcomings,

00:48.167 --> 00:51.066
her advice over the past couple
of months has been exemplary.

00:51.067 --> 00:53.333
- But you and Sarah...
- Yes.

00:53.334 --> 00:55.333
I would marry her tomorrow if I could.

00:55.334 --> 00:58.299
But I've made this bed. And
perhaps I have to lie in it.

00:58.300 --> 01:00.899
ELIZABETH: So... Regina.

01:00.900 --> 01:03.600
SARAH: I'm sure she
murdered Milly Davis.

01:03.601 --> 01:05.966
Now, you remember what I
said about a roman á clef?

01:05.967 --> 01:08.366
Readers recognize the
truth behind the fiction.

01:08.367 --> 01:10.500
And reputations can be slayed.

01:10.501 --> 01:12.199
Once you've delivered your manuscript,

01:12.200 --> 01:14.366
it could give it proof absolute.

01:14.367 --> 01:17.234
Regina would provide it herself.

01:17.900 --> 01:19.767
Factions will be forming.

01:19.768 --> 01:21.800
I trust I can rely upon you.

01:21.801 --> 01:23.233
Thank you for lunch.

01:23.234 --> 01:24.700
<i>Grazie. A domani.</i>

01:24.701 --> 01:26.299
GINO: She shouldn't be around Regina.

01:26.300 --> 01:28.466
Grandmother's plan won't
work unless they're close.

01:28.467 --> 01:29.932
You're using her.

01:29.933 --> 01:31.932
There is something I need to do

01:31.933 --> 01:34.202
if I can bring Anna and Gino home.

01:35.227 --> 01:39.261
- sync and corrections by Mr.C -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:39.467 --> 01:42.967
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION,
VEHICLES PASSING)

01:48.967 --> 01:51.067
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

01:57.567 --> 01:59.234
ANNA: Sure you won't come?

02:01.834 --> 02:03.834
It's nothing to do with me.

02:10.366 --> 02:12.701
If she asks how we are?

02:15.634 --> 02:17.100
She has to know sometime.

02:18.501 --> 02:20.234
I'll play it by ear.

02:22.167 --> 02:23.801
Thank you.

02:30.434 --> 02:32.299
(DOOR OPENS)

02:32.300 --> 02:34.634
(DOG BARKING, SHEEP BLEATING)

02:36.768 --> 02:39.166
Roy would have you back, you know.

02:39.167 --> 02:40.966
Oh, I'll find something.

02:40.967 --> 02:44.167
Might even manage a spare
room here if they keep me on.

02:46.100 --> 02:48.834
Can't believe how big
he's got in two weeks.

02:49.868 --> 02:51.701
Bye-bye, you.

02:54.300 --> 02:55.533
He needs a name.

02:55.534 --> 02:58.066
Oh, he's stuck with it his whole life.

02:58.067 --> 02:59.899
It merits thought.

02:59.900 --> 03:00.999
Thanks for the offer.

03:01.000 --> 03:02.767
Bed's there if you need it.

03:02.768 --> 03:03.933
Ah.

03:04.801 --> 03:07.200
You two and his nibs is
enough for one home.

03:08.134 --> 03:10.033
But expect visits.

03:14.768 --> 03:17.700
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

03:17.701 --> 03:20.234
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

03:25.701 --> 03:26.666
Grandmother.

03:26.667 --> 03:28.633
Oh, travel becomes you.

03:28.634 --> 03:30.466
Oh. (CHUCKLES)

03:30.467 --> 03:32.633
Love becomes <i>you.</i>

03:32.634 --> 03:33.834
May I?

03:34.367 --> 03:36.133
Oh.

03:36.134 --> 03:38.433
You go away and voilà.

03:38.434 --> 03:39.533
It's lovely.

03:39.534 --> 03:41.133
Congratulations, Grandmother.

03:41.134 --> 03:42.634
Thank you.

03:44.634 --> 03:46.134
Gino?

03:47.434 --> 03:50.733
Oh, it was a long flight.

03:50.734 --> 03:53.133
He still disapproves of our plan.

03:53.134 --> 03:55.032
Not of tackling Regina.

03:55.033 --> 03:57.133
Of utilizing Rose?

03:57.134 --> 03:59.834
He says her letters show a change.

04:00.834 --> 04:02.566
(SIGHS)

04:02.567 --> 04:04.367
Would it help if I spoke to him?

04:05.434 --> 04:07.133
Probably not.

04:07.134 --> 04:08.501
May I try?

04:09.501 --> 04:11.100
If you wish.

04:11.601 --> 04:15.800
Well, Anna, what I wish
is George disabused,

04:15.801 --> 04:18.966
Regina toppled, and
all damage redressed.

04:18.966 --> 04:21.833
Then we can get on with our lives.

04:21.834 --> 04:23.233
Did you send him the telegram?

04:23.234 --> 04:24.634
This morning.

04:25.134 --> 04:28.466
And our... incendiary device?

04:28.467 --> 04:30.867
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

04:30.868 --> 04:32.500
You've read it?

04:32.501 --> 04:34.466
Beautifully written. Incendiary indeed.

04:34.467 --> 04:36.066
ELIZABETH: Oh, good.

04:36.067 --> 04:40.032
Well, Italy first, then schemes.

04:40.033 --> 04:42.733
I gave Anna three coins
for the Trevi Fountain.

04:42.734 --> 04:44.833
Perhaps the fountain
has blessed all of us.

04:44.834 --> 04:46.100
Mm.

04:47.868 --> 04:50.134
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

04:51.300 --> 04:53.099
Anna and Gino are resting at Carolyn's

04:53.100 --> 04:54.899
before the final leg home.

04:54.900 --> 04:57.566
So, no explanation for
the sudden return?

04:57.567 --> 04:59.601
Mother's engagement, I presume.

05:00.167 --> 05:02.167
They'd like to see me
as soon as possible.

05:03.200 --> 05:05.199
I'll go on the weekend.

05:05.200 --> 05:06.734
We'll both go.

05:07.200 --> 05:08.966
Are you sure?

05:08.967 --> 05:09.932
Of course.

05:09.933 --> 05:11.366
(SPOON TAPS)

05:11.367 --> 05:13.701
- Thank you, Rose.
- Yes, ma'am.

05:14.634 --> 05:17.032
There'll be the inevitable tensions.

05:17.033 --> 05:18.899
Well, not from me.

05:18.900 --> 05:20.899
Our Canberra months
have been too rewarding

05:20.900 --> 05:22.367
to be sullied by old grudges.

05:23.501 --> 05:25.534
And there is the added
matter of the baby.

05:26.834 --> 05:28.567
I'd like to welcome our travelers home.

05:29.768 --> 05:32.366
Let me prove I can stay well out of it.

05:32.367 --> 05:34.167
I'll stay at the guest cottage.

05:35.033 --> 05:36.100
It might be best.

05:37.634 --> 05:39.701
Whatever's most conducive to calm.

05:42.334 --> 05:45.100
Our arrangement has borne fruit here.

05:45.933 --> 05:48.300
Give me my chance there, too.

05:52.434 --> 05:53.367
All right.

05:54.334 --> 05:55.534
Thank you.

05:57.768 --> 05:59.433
ANNA: We're finished
before we've started

05:59.434 --> 06:01.133
if Regina doesn't return with him.

06:01.134 --> 06:04.366
And lose the opportunity to
trumpet her political triumphs?

06:04.367 --> 06:06.767
- She'll come.
- Undone by her worst impulses.

06:06.768 --> 06:08.533
Which makes it all the more delicious.

06:08.534 --> 06:10.233
As is this...

06:10.234 --> 06:13.733
"The mundane knife scraping
of Dot cutting cake

06:13.734 --> 06:16.999
contrasting sharply with her own
view of the lethal crystals

06:17.000 --> 06:19.400
dissolving swiftly into the tonic."

06:19.401 --> 06:21.533
I have reading to do.

06:21.534 --> 06:24.566
And I will visit Gino.

06:24.567 --> 06:25.700
Fine.

06:25.701 --> 06:27.300
But only if you're sure.

06:29.100 --> 06:30.367
If you are going...

06:31.367 --> 06:34.134
there are larger problems
than his attitude about Rose.

06:37.967 --> 06:41.167
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

06:41.768 --> 06:43.700
Brings back memories.

06:43.701 --> 06:45.834
(BABY COOING)

06:49.967 --> 06:51.966
How were your boys as babies?

06:51.967 --> 06:53.099
(CHUCKLES) Oh.

06:53.100 --> 06:56.366
There's nothing he can dish up
that I haven't seen or heard.

06:56.367 --> 06:58.066
Oh, a long time ago.

06:58.067 --> 06:59.366
You up for it?

06:59.367 --> 07:01.367
That's what cotton wool's for.

07:06.634 --> 07:09.032
You sure it won't affect you and Dawn?

07:09.033 --> 07:11.134
Might help, truth be told.

07:11.801 --> 07:15.800
You being gone has given her notions.

07:15.801 --> 07:17.566
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

07:17.567 --> 07:19.166
Wasn't that the general idea?

07:19.167 --> 07:20.834
Oh, it made sense first up.

07:21.501 --> 07:23.833
I thought you were
enjoying stepping out.

07:23.834 --> 07:25.833
Stepping out is fine.

07:25.834 --> 07:28.299
I'm just not so sure
about the stepping up...

07:28.300 --> 07:30.134
to the altar.

07:31.367 --> 07:33.566
Oh.

07:33.567 --> 07:35.099
Keeping company's fine,

07:35.100 --> 07:38.433
but marriage, it's a whole other brew.

07:38.434 --> 07:40.300
Don't go giving her false hopes.

07:41.667 --> 07:44.500
I'll be too busy being Uncle Roy

07:44.501 --> 07:48.033
to be worried about being
hubby and dad to anyone.

07:50.100 --> 07:52.033
You thought I'd be protecting <i>you,</i> eh?

07:53.134 --> 07:55.333
Well, I, for one, hope you stop running.

07:55.334 --> 07:56.700
What about you?

07:56.701 --> 07:58.700
I've stopped.

07:58.701 --> 08:01.032
For better or worse.

08:01.033 --> 08:03.366
(VEHICLES PASSING)

08:03.367 --> 08:05.932
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

08:05.933 --> 08:07.533
Oh.

08:07.534 --> 08:09.032
- <i>Entrare.</i>
- (CHUCKLES)

08:09.033 --> 08:10.566
Sorry. Come in.

08:10.567 --> 08:12.700
Adjusting to English again.

08:12.701 --> 08:14.768
(CLEARS THROAT) Yes.

08:15.534 --> 08:18.400
Anna passed on your congratulations.

08:18.401 --> 08:20.099
Douglas is a good man.

08:20.100 --> 08:21.401
He is.

08:24.734 --> 08:26.234
Ah. Please.

08:29.834 --> 08:34.433
Uh, Gino, I felt I should
justify my choices.

08:34.433 --> 08:37.366
- Yeah. You don't have to...
- I think I do.

08:38.167 --> 08:40.732
Being summoned back to intrigue

08:40.734 --> 08:43.167
must contrast with what
you left in Italy.

08:44.134 --> 08:45.366
Yes.

08:45.367 --> 08:47.100
How are your dear parents?

08:47.601 --> 08:51.033
It was good... being a
whole family again.

08:51.601 --> 08:55.933
All the more reason to apologize
for hurrying you home.

08:56.701 --> 08:57.833
Now, regarding Rose,

08:57.834 --> 09:01.800
I do believe that the
ends justify the means.

09:01.801 --> 09:02.833
She cannot become

09:02.834 --> 09:04.633
- what she's not inclined to be.
- And what do you...

09:04.634 --> 09:07.300
Or do you prefer to see
Regina go unpunished?

09:08.701 --> 09:13.433
She must be dealt with, Gino,
before she has the chance

09:13.434 --> 09:16.600
to harm George's dealings with his son,

09:16.601 --> 09:19.267
possibly even the baby himself.

09:21.267 --> 09:23.867
This is what I was glad to be away from.

09:23.868 --> 09:25.801
I understand.

09:29.167 --> 09:31.401
Anna told me your sad news.

09:36.634 --> 09:37.601
I'm so sorry.

09:38.967 --> 09:41.099
I just have to get used to it.

09:41.100 --> 09:42.899
There's always adoption.

09:42.900 --> 09:43.834
No.

09:44.900 --> 09:47.767
Well, we love Georgie no
less for his origins.

09:47.768 --> 09:49.366
And you'll love the new baby more.

09:49.367 --> 09:51.234
Of course you will.

09:52.100 --> 09:54.167
I wanted my own son.

09:55.900 --> 09:57.801
What's our marriage now?

09:59.100 --> 10:00.233
That is foolishness.

10:00.234 --> 10:02.033
Is it?

10:03.000 --> 10:07.400
You've overcome so much to
be together, me included.

10:07.401 --> 10:08.899
Oh, you <i>will</i> weather this.

10:08.900 --> 10:10.768
I will never hold our child.

10:11.933 --> 10:13.801
But you will hold Anna.

10:17.967 --> 10:19.701
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

10:21.000 --> 10:27.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:34.434 --> 10:39.067
Can't have Gino and Mrs. Poletti
coming home to a dirty house.

10:39.868 --> 10:41.500
It <i>is</i> rather sudden.

10:41.501 --> 10:43.299
Must be homesick.

10:43.300 --> 10:45.467
Sarah's already back at Roy's.

10:45.933 --> 10:47.533
What about you?

10:47.534 --> 10:50.534
Well, I'll keep on with
the job if Gino wants.

10:52.501 --> 10:53.667
What are you doing Sunday?

10:55.300 --> 10:57.366
Not much.

10:57.367 --> 10:59.433
A friend of mine's having a
birthday party in Sydney,

10:59.434 --> 11:00.733
mostly our kind.

11:00.734 --> 11:01.534
Come.

11:03.134 --> 11:04.233
Am I invited?

11:04.234 --> 11:05.601
You will be if I ask.

11:06.167 --> 11:07.800
You'll never met anyone here.

11:07.801 --> 11:09.633
(CHUCKLES)

11:09.634 --> 11:10.600
Nice thought.

11:10.601 --> 11:12.533
Uh...

11:12.534 --> 11:17.801
your kind of our kind aren't... my kind.

11:18.367 --> 11:19.366
We get on.

11:19.367 --> 11:21.533
But we've known each other
since we were kids.

11:21.534 --> 11:23.967
I'd just be rough trade to them.

11:25.567 --> 11:26.867
Try.

11:26.868 --> 11:27.768
For me.

11:30.834 --> 11:32.299
If it helps you, fine.

11:32.300 --> 11:35.867
But don't expect too much from me.

11:35.868 --> 11:37.167
I'll pick you up midday Saturday.

11:38.534 --> 11:41.299
See you at the intersection.
Saves questions.

11:41.300 --> 11:43.067
Be good to get out.

11:46.900 --> 11:48.501
Thank you.

11:56.100 --> 11:57.466
Gino?

11:57.467 --> 12:01.534
Gino, I-I thought that we
were staying till morning.

12:03.033 --> 12:04.401
I want to get home.

12:05.367 --> 12:06.701
Excuse me.

12:07.234 --> 12:09.233
It'll be better there. We
can take the late train.

12:09.234 --> 12:10.366
If we must.

12:10.367 --> 12:11.434
Might you drive us?

12:12.601 --> 12:13.833
Of course.

12:13.834 --> 12:14.966
You've got plans.

12:14.967 --> 12:16.133
I can change them.

12:16.134 --> 12:17.199
Done.

12:17.200 --> 12:19.233
We can take care of ourselves.

12:19.234 --> 12:20.999
But thank you.

12:21.000 --> 12:22.933
Let me know what you decide.

12:23.933 --> 12:25.966
D-Did Grandmother say something?

12:25.967 --> 12:28.334
- It's nothing to do with her.
- Well, what, then?

12:30.134 --> 12:31.299
No. You're right. You're right.

12:31.300 --> 12:35.099
We're... We're more likely to
get it into perspective there.

12:35.100 --> 12:36.701
I want to.

12:38.667 --> 12:40.100
I hope.

12:40.967 --> 12:41.966
But right now...

12:41.967 --> 12:43.533
Well, we've been days in the air,

12:43.534 --> 12:45.166
and we've... we've hardly slept,

12:45.167 --> 12:48.666
and... we only just found out.

12:48.667 --> 12:49.768
So you're right.

12:51.167 --> 12:52.533
Yeah.

12:52.534 --> 12:55.367
It'll be... It'll be better at home.

13:09.367 --> 13:12.167
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

13:13.501 --> 13:16.401
I thought we said no more
beautiful days in dark rooms.

13:17.367 --> 13:20.134
I've got the most shocking head.

13:21.401 --> 13:22.200
Livvy.

13:23.501 --> 13:25.534
You can't go on like this.

13:26.200 --> 13:28.467
I am trying to move past it.

13:31.067 --> 13:34.033
I just can't help but feel...

13:35.667 --> 13:37.634
so foolish.

13:40.501 --> 13:43.333
Perhaps I should cancel
my weekend plans.

13:43.334 --> 13:45.633
Don't <i>you</i> be foolish.

13:45.634 --> 13:46.967
Go.

13:49.534 --> 13:51.567
I want to be strong.

13:52.834 --> 13:54.300
I <i>will</i> be strong.

13:56.967 --> 13:59.033
As long as you need.

14:00.401 --> 14:02.801
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

14:10.434 --> 14:12.434
There you go.

14:14.601 --> 14:16.032
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

14:16.033 --> 14:17.366
It's mealtime.

14:17.367 --> 14:19.932
ROY: You've got a visitor
when you're ready.

14:19.933 --> 14:21.999
Who?

14:22.000 --> 14:23.367
James.

14:30.300 --> 14:31.734
Come on.

14:33.667 --> 14:36.334
It looks like you're
gonna meet your brother.

14:39.634 --> 14:41.134
Hello there.

14:42.033 --> 14:43.366
Have you decided on a name?

14:43.367 --> 14:45.768
Uh, no, not yet.

14:46.434 --> 14:48.033
Well, look at you.

14:48.567 --> 14:50.433
You're fast asleep, aren't you?

14:50.434 --> 14:51.633
Yes, you are.

14:51.634 --> 14:52.900
- Yes, you...
- Thank you.

14:57.367 --> 14:59.200
I'm not here for Father.

15:01.601 --> 15:04.233
I hope you can understand.

15:04.234 --> 15:06.167
It's between the two of you.

15:07.768 --> 15:09.434
I'll leave you to it.

15:10.967 --> 15:12.367
Thanks, Roy.

15:15.933 --> 15:17.434
Sit down.

15:20.234 --> 15:22.366
I'm here for Olivia.

15:22.367 --> 15:24.234
She's extremely low.

15:25.000 --> 15:26.366
I've tried helping, but...

15:26.367 --> 15:27.734
What's wrong?

15:28.501 --> 15:30.300
She's been dealt a rather large blow.

15:31.667 --> 15:35.099
The man she was following to
England has severed all ties.

15:35.100 --> 15:36.534
He's left her in a funk.

15:37.900 --> 15:39.700
When was this?

15:39.701 --> 15:41.734
Just after he was born.

15:43.734 --> 15:45.433
She's tried lifting herself out of it,

15:45.434 --> 15:48.300
and... I don't seem to
be of very much use.

15:50.734 --> 15:53.133
If I encouraged her to reach out to you?

15:53.134 --> 15:54.966
I know you're trying to keep
your distance from the family.

15:54.967 --> 15:56.900
It's not that. It's...

15:57.367 --> 15:59.367
She and I have had our differences.

16:00.567 --> 16:03.534
But she admires you very much.

16:05.701 --> 16:07.534
You've always been <i>my</i> savior.

16:09.367 --> 16:11.600
I do seem to have built that reputation.

16:11.601 --> 16:13.534
(CHUCKLES)

16:14.367 --> 16:16.501
If you think I can help her...

16:18.801 --> 16:19.800
Thank you.

16:19.801 --> 16:22.634
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

16:25.367 --> 16:27.032
Any message for Father when he returns?

16:27.033 --> 16:30.100
Um, just that his son is well.

16:32.300 --> 16:36.033
And he's welcome... of course.

16:38.300 --> 16:41.299
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

16:41.300 --> 16:43.099
Is that all, ma'am?

16:43.100 --> 16:44.333
It is.

16:44.334 --> 16:45.768
Good night, dear.

16:46.300 --> 16:49.701
I can't wait to be back... see Gino.

16:50.300 --> 16:54.733
And show the other locals how
sophisticated you've become.

16:54.734 --> 16:56.167
That too.

16:58.100 --> 17:01.200
We both have things to show Inverness.

17:03.167 --> 17:05.099
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

17:09.200 --> 17:10.900
Hello, you.

17:13.000 --> 17:14.434
Hello...

17:15.166 --> 17:16.634
David.

17:19.401 --> 17:21.534
How do you feel about that?

17:23.134 --> 17:24.834
David.

17:26.300 --> 17:28.134
David.

17:32.300 --> 17:34.300
For now just David.

17:34.734 --> 17:36.467
Yes.

17:39.868 --> 17:42.099
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

17:42.100 --> 17:44.334
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

18:11.367 --> 18:13.032
On approach.

18:13.033 --> 18:15.600
I'll remain scarce until
it's time to play my part.

18:15.601 --> 18:17.199
Oh, it must work.

18:17.200 --> 18:18.800
DOUGLAS: You've been
planning it long enough.

18:18.801 --> 18:21.167
Things can still go awry.

18:22.933 --> 18:24.801
Fingers crossed.

18:26.167 --> 18:29.033
(UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

18:54.000 --> 18:55.768
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

18:58.834 --> 19:00.067
Welcome.

19:00.634 --> 19:02.767
From the cut and thrust of the capital.

19:02.768 --> 19:04.800
To the cut and thrust of home.

19:04.801 --> 19:06.700
- Congratulations again.
- Thank you.

19:06.701 --> 19:09.433
I've been looking forward to
the good oil on Canberra.

19:09.434 --> 19:10.767
GEORGE: Well, there's plenty of that.

19:10.768 --> 19:14.600
I insisted on coming simply
to add my own good wishes.

19:14.601 --> 19:15.999
(SMOOCHES)

19:16.000 --> 19:17.433
I shall abide by all rules

19:17.434 --> 19:20.433
and keep whatever distance is necessary.

19:20.434 --> 19:21.767
Perhaps your new beginning

19:21.768 --> 19:24.966
might contribute to warmer
feelings generally.

19:24.967 --> 19:26.099
Perhaps.

19:26.100 --> 19:28.401
Uh, ma'am, your cases.

19:29.100 --> 19:31.134
The gray room, I think.

19:31.634 --> 19:33.367
Not the guest cottage?

19:33.834 --> 19:35.834
As you said, new beginnings.

19:41.567 --> 19:42.801
Come.

19:48.534 --> 19:51.633
(SIGHS) They just arrived.

19:51.634 --> 19:52.433
Good.

19:52.434 --> 19:54.634
I'll do the courtesies and be off.

19:55.367 --> 19:57.366
Your father won't be offended?

19:57.367 --> 19:59.701
He said not on the telephone.

20:01.134 --> 20:05.133
Have you sensed anything
strange the last few days?

20:05.134 --> 20:06.434
How so?

20:07.367 --> 20:09.734
Low-voiced conversations.

20:10.501 --> 20:12.899
The sense we're being
excluded from something.

20:12.900 --> 20:15.167
No one is keen on Regina returning.

20:16.000 --> 20:17.634
It may be just that.

20:23.033 --> 20:24.801
If you'd like to get away...

20:26.567 --> 20:29.533
I'm boring even myself.

20:29.534 --> 20:30.900
I'll spare you the misery.

20:37.734 --> 20:39.467
See Sarah.

20:41.734 --> 20:43.966
I behaved so poorly over Harry.

20:43.967 --> 20:45.767
That was months ago.

20:45.768 --> 20:46.933
Her offer is genuine.

20:51.334 --> 20:52.767
(SIGHS) I really should stay.

20:52.768 --> 20:55.868
Go to your gathering, please.

20:57.300 --> 20:58.868
At least one of us should be happy.

21:02.501 --> 21:04.401
The minute you're gone...

21:06.501 --> 21:07.967
I will see her.

21:14.534 --> 21:16.933
Nice that you're back in the house.

21:17.734 --> 21:19.501
I'll finish that.

21:21.367 --> 21:24.233
Question the other staff discreetly.

21:24.234 --> 21:25.366
See what's to tell.

21:25.367 --> 21:26.299
Yes, ma'am.

21:26.300 --> 21:29.066
And pop over to the Polettis'.
I know you're anxious to.

21:29.067 --> 21:30.466
Thank you.

21:30.467 --> 21:32.966
See what Gino has to say.

21:32.967 --> 21:35.167
He's an easier nut to crack than Anna.

21:39.734 --> 21:41.367
Something's afoot.

21:43.434 --> 21:45.466
Thank you for making the
effort with Regina.

21:45.467 --> 21:48.333
Oh, courtesy costs little,

21:48.334 --> 21:51.299
especially given that I'll soon be gone.

21:51.300 --> 21:53.567
We're finally taking that
Middle Eastern trip.

21:54.868 --> 21:56.032
That's wonderful.

21:56.033 --> 21:58.099
We'll reside in Sydney when we return.

21:58.100 --> 21:59.600
We're marrying overseas.

21:59.601 --> 22:02.400
The usual malarkey's more of
an embarrassment at our age

22:02.401 --> 22:03.600
than anything else.

22:03.601 --> 22:05.501
Unless you'd be too disappointed.

22:06.567 --> 22:08.033
Whatever you see fit.

22:08.567 --> 22:10.366
We'd be taking St. Andrew's Cathedral

22:10.367 --> 22:12.600
if Prudence Swanson had her way.

22:12.601 --> 22:15.733
Yes. Well, it does seem a
choice between all or no fuss.

22:15.734 --> 22:17.567
Spot on.

22:18.567 --> 22:21.700
Anyway, um, you have things to discuss.

22:21.701 --> 22:22.966
Oh, Douglas, you don't have to...

22:22.967 --> 22:24.899
Yes, I do. You'll understand.

22:24.900 --> 22:26.834
I'll be off doing my bit, then.

22:27.334 --> 22:28.334
Good luck.

22:31.033 --> 22:32.633
Mysterious.

22:32.634 --> 22:35.467
George, there's something
I want you to read.

22:37.367 --> 22:38.566
Anna's novel.

22:38.567 --> 22:40.366
And so much more than that.

22:40.367 --> 22:42.299
Hm. I'm looking forward to it.

22:42.300 --> 22:44.300
(KNOCK, DOOR OPENS)

22:44.768 --> 22:47.700
Ah. There you are. You're
dashing off, aren't you?

22:47.701 --> 22:49.566
- A quick word first.
- Of course.

22:49.567 --> 22:51.501
And then come back... please.

22:52.334 --> 22:53.466
I'll read it later.

22:53.467 --> 22:55.700
No. Uh, now.

22:55.701 --> 22:56.834
Please.

22:58.967 --> 23:00.367
All right.

23:06.834 --> 23:09.234
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

23:13.834 --> 23:15.768
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

23:17.401 --> 23:18.933
Come.

23:21.367 --> 23:24.733
Uh, Lizzie and George are
poring over the accounts.

23:24.734 --> 23:28.067
I just wondered if you'd
be up for a canter.

23:30.300 --> 23:32.700
I was thinking of putting my head down.

23:32.701 --> 23:35.300
Oh. Well, some other time, then.

23:36.467 --> 23:38.167
The fresh air will do me good.

23:40.334 --> 23:42.100
Excellent.

23:42.834 --> 23:46.467
Right. Well, uh, I'll
just get things ready.

23:47.300 --> 23:49.166
(DOOR CLOSES)

23:49.167 --> 23:50.899
JAMES: You don't mind my
roping Sarah in, then?

23:50.900 --> 23:53.900
Quite the reverse.
Should I talk to Olivia?

23:54.834 --> 23:56.299
If she brings it up.

23:56.300 --> 23:57.833
Of course.

23:57.834 --> 24:00.366
Any idea of what she intends to do now?

24:00.367 --> 24:01.400
(SIGHS)

24:01.401 --> 24:03.167
That's the problem.

24:04.100 --> 24:06.000
- I'll see you Tuesday.
- Mm.

24:10.967 --> 24:14.800
Do you know what this
business is with Anna's book?

24:14.801 --> 24:17.366
I got a very firm "no" when I
asked to read it yesterday.

24:17.367 --> 24:18.966
It's being firmly foisted on me.

24:18.967 --> 24:20.400
Without a chance to draw breath?

24:20.401 --> 24:21.734
Seemingly.

24:22.501 --> 24:24.533
Perhaps they value your
keen literary eye.

24:24.534 --> 24:27.367
(LAUGHS) I suspect not.

24:28.634 --> 24:30.299
Oh.

24:30.300 --> 24:34.367
Sarah said you're welcome to drop by...
anytime.

24:37.134 --> 24:39.867
(ENGINE STARTS, REVS)

24:39.868 --> 24:42.768
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

24:50.100 --> 24:52.133
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

24:52.134 --> 24:55.032
This will have to wait. I'm sorry.
I'm off to see Sarah.

24:55.033 --> 24:57.333
It can't wait. It's waited long enough.

24:57.334 --> 24:59.999
- Sarah...
- Sarah wants this.

25:00.000 --> 25:02.768
Now, I've marked the
most pertinent pages.

25:15.933 --> 25:18.634
JACK: Well, he's making
up for a shaky start.

25:19.534 --> 25:21.100
He's a bonny bouncing boy.

25:21.701 --> 25:23.366
Aren't you?

25:23.367 --> 25:24.566
David.

25:24.567 --> 25:25.767
Sorry?

25:25.768 --> 25:27.367
His name.

25:27.868 --> 25:29.768
His name is David.

25:30.567 --> 25:32.033
It's my brother.

25:33.334 --> 25:35.333
His death brought me back to Australia.

25:35.334 --> 25:37.967
I'd never have been on that
ship if it weren't for him.

25:38.467 --> 25:40.667
George and I would never have met.

25:41.134 --> 25:42.700
Well, he deserves recognition.

25:42.701 --> 25:44.100
I thought so.

25:45.567 --> 25:48.634
I'm ready to fill in
that birth certificate.

25:49.467 --> 25:51.166
Surname?

25:51.167 --> 25:53.634
Yes. I've decided on that too.

25:54.434 --> 25:55.700
Well, shouldn't you wait?

25:55.701 --> 25:57.133
With what's in play at Ash Park...

25:57.134 --> 25:59.134
Nothing there will change my decision.

26:00.033 --> 26:01.100
You're sure?

26:02.701 --> 26:04.167
Absolutely.

26:05.401 --> 26:07.634
(CLOCK TICKING)

26:14.501 --> 26:16.700
Sarah has read this?

26:16.701 --> 26:19.433
She is very familiar with the content.

26:19.434 --> 26:20.967
Keep going.

26:26.300 --> 26:29.334
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

26:31.734 --> 26:32.768
No going back.

26:33.834 --> 26:35.567
No desire to.

26:39.300 --> 26:41.299
(DOOR OPENS)

26:41.300 --> 26:43.066
(WHISTLES)

26:43.067 --> 26:46.067
So... who is she?

26:46.567 --> 26:48.133
What do you mean?

26:48.134 --> 26:51.334
Well, you're all... spruced up.

26:52.300 --> 26:54.299
- My sister.
- Amy?

26:54.300 --> 26:55.899
- Yeah.
- Oh.

26:55.900 --> 26:58.500
- Say hello for me, huh?
- I will.

26:58.501 --> 26:59.933
Maybe she'll have a friend.

27:00.567 --> 27:02.533
It'd be a shame for
that Californian poppy

27:02.534 --> 27:04.233
to go to waste, hmm?

27:04.234 --> 27:06.166
(CHUCKLES)

27:06.167 --> 27:08.099
You want a lift to the station?

27:08.100 --> 27:10.166
Uh, gonna hitch down.

27:10.167 --> 27:11.366
ROSE: <i>Buon giorno!</i>

27:11.367 --> 27:13.100
Ah! <i>Ciao, ragazza!</i>

27:15.367 --> 27:16.833
<i>Come stai?</i>

27:16.834 --> 27:18.601
<i>Va bene, grazie.</i>

27:19.501 --> 27:20.600
When'd you get back?

27:20.601 --> 27:21.899
Just now.

27:21.900 --> 27:23.366
Couldn't wait to see if I'd imported

27:23.367 --> 27:25.601
that, uh, Italian husband, no?

27:26.200 --> 27:27.100
Is that him?

27:27.834 --> 27:30.299
That's Harry, my farmhand.

27:30.300 --> 27:32.567
Oh, yeah. He came to Ash Park once.

27:33.467 --> 27:34.434
Hey, Harry.

27:34.933 --> 27:36.633
Rose likes Californian poppy.

27:36.634 --> 27:39.032
Oh, it stinks. So cheap.

27:39.033 --> 27:40.434
Yuck.

27:42.300 --> 27:44.667
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

27:46.067 --> 27:47.501
I'll see you Tuesday, huh?

27:49.033 --> 27:51.900
- I won't need the room long.
- Oh, no rush.

27:53.033 --> 27:54.367
Rose.

27:58.734 --> 28:01.200
He's not Italian... but he's single.

28:01.967 --> 28:03.100
I can do better.

28:04.100 --> 28:05.567
He's handsome, but...

28:06.134 --> 28:08.501
It's been so exciting.

28:09.367 --> 28:12.400
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

28:12.401 --> 28:13.700
Dashing Dan.

28:13.701 --> 28:16.899
(EXHALES DEEPLY) Took a
bit of getting away.

28:16.900 --> 28:19.100
Not too many questions?

28:19.768 --> 28:21.734
I never enjoy the lies.

28:22.367 --> 28:23.767
Self-protection.

28:23.768 --> 28:25.701
(ENGINE STARTS)

28:29.501 --> 28:31.401
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

28:43.768 --> 28:46.768
(HORSE NEIGHS, SNORTS)

28:50.134 --> 28:51.601
Invigorating.

28:52.401 --> 28:54.800
Your hand of friendship surprises.

28:54.801 --> 28:55.768
But pleases.

28:56.734 --> 28:59.999
I'm intent on healing the rift.

29:00.000 --> 29:03.032
Lizzie doesn't need the
unnecessary strain.

29:03.033 --> 29:06.100
Nor do I, so thank you.

29:06.667 --> 29:07.966
Perhaps we should get back.

29:07.967 --> 29:10.233
Another bracing dash first, hmm?

29:10.234 --> 29:12.000
(CLICKS TONGUE) Come on.

29:13.601 --> 29:16.167
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

29:19.467 --> 29:21.433
It's outrageous slander.

29:21.434 --> 29:23.266
Anna can't possibly publish.

29:23.267 --> 29:25.433
So you've read between the lines?

29:25.434 --> 29:27.434
The similarities are glaring.

29:28.768 --> 29:30.366
She's saying Regina is...

29:30.367 --> 29:32.401
Finish it and then we can talk.

29:33.000 --> 29:34.601
I insist.

29:40.834 --> 29:43.533
Thanks for the scarf. It's beautiful.

29:43.534 --> 29:46.500
You should see Mrs.
Bligh's scarves, though.

29:46.501 --> 29:47.767
There's this silk one.

29:47.768 --> 29:49.566
Just the feel of it.

29:49.567 --> 29:51.999
She lets you wear them? That's lovely.

29:52.000 --> 29:53.601
I try them on when she goes out.

29:54.167 --> 29:55.134
Guess what.

29:55.933 --> 29:58.366
I've got a boyfriend... sort of.

29:58.367 --> 30:00.032
Oh, it's a wonder you've got time.

30:00.033 --> 30:01.999
He works next door. He sneaks over.

30:02.000 --> 30:03.600
Oh, you'll get yourself fired.

30:03.601 --> 30:05.600
What does Mrs. Bligh think of that?

30:05.601 --> 30:08.400
Mrs. Bligh doesn't mind
if it's not too much.

30:08.401 --> 30:10.500
I mean, she's a woman of the world.

30:10.501 --> 30:12.400
Don't tell Mr. Bligh.

30:12.401 --> 30:14.767
You'll get yourself into trouble again.

30:14.768 --> 30:16.966
Listen to you, stuffy pants.

30:16.967 --> 30:19.932
You can take care of
yourself, can't you?

30:19.933 --> 30:21.400
I should go and greet Father.

30:21.401 --> 30:22.633
Could you drop us over?

30:22.634 --> 30:23.932
Of course.

30:23.933 --> 30:25.367
I'll get the key.

30:26.334 --> 30:27.966
Aren't you going?

30:27.967 --> 30:31.299
Anna's, uh, got things to talk about.

30:31.300 --> 30:32.333
What things?

30:32.334 --> 30:33.299
What?

30:33.300 --> 30:35.033
What's Anna got to talk about?

30:35.868 --> 30:38.567
It's just... it feels
strange over there.

30:39.367 --> 30:40.933
Well, strange how?

30:41.933 --> 30:45.501
Everyone's almost too nice to...
to Mrs. Bligh.

30:46.067 --> 30:48.833
You know, they're awful
to her most of the time.

30:48.834 --> 30:51.099
They must have their reasons.

30:51.100 --> 30:53.466
Anna's not very nice to her either.

30:53.467 --> 30:56.100
- I'm just saying.
- You're best out of it, Rosa.

30:57.134 --> 30:59.133
It's old Mrs. Bligh. It's her fault.

30:59.134 --> 31:00.733
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Don't take sides, huh?

31:00.734 --> 31:02.633
Mrs. Bligh's one of the
nicest people ever.

31:02.634 --> 31:03.600
Maybe...

31:03.601 --> 31:04.566
What?

31:04.567 --> 31:06.433
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

31:06.434 --> 31:07.700
Maybe she's...

31:07.701 --> 31:09.567
- Are you ready?
- Yeah.

31:10.701 --> 31:11.899
What?

31:11.900 --> 31:13.633
Nothing.

31:13.634 --> 31:17.366
Rosa was just saying how
much she likes Regina.

31:17.367 --> 31:20.533
Of course. Yes. She's been good to you.

31:20.534 --> 31:22.900
We'll put your bike in the back.

31:28.067 --> 31:29.967
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

31:31.300 --> 31:33.567
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

31:35.434 --> 31:38.299
He's very young for a brother-in-law.

31:38.300 --> 31:39.701
Oh.

31:41.067 --> 31:42.366
He's beautiful.

31:42.367 --> 31:44.067
I'm biased.

31:44.967 --> 31:45.933
And happy.

31:47.033 --> 31:48.666
I'm sorry.

31:48.667 --> 31:51.033
- I'm sorry to break in on it.
- Olivia.

31:52.501 --> 31:54.434
I have to be strong.

31:56.434 --> 31:59.501
I want... to be stronger.

32:02.634 --> 32:04.534
You're so strong.

32:10.401 --> 32:11.967
Tell me.

32:15.367 --> 32:20.768
I've felt a sense of who I am...
or might be...

32:22.367 --> 32:24.367
twice in my life.

32:25.900 --> 32:30.300
At the Hunt Ball, when James
first looked at me and...

32:31.367 --> 32:34.033
I thought, really saw me.

32:35.300 --> 32:38.033
I'd felt invisible until then.

32:38.701 --> 32:42.967
And when Lloyd recognized...

32:45.501 --> 32:47.534
the woman craving release.

32:51.300 --> 32:53.300
Both proved an illusion.

32:54.367 --> 32:55.966
Which makes my whole life one.

32:55.967 --> 32:56.966
Surely...

32:56.967 --> 33:00.400
From wallflower to... to
marriage of convenience

33:00.401 --> 33:05.233
to... confused mother
to naive adulteress.

33:05.234 --> 33:09.366
Mistaking a roué for a future.

33:09.367 --> 33:13.199
Lloyd got his entrée
into London society.

33:13.200 --> 33:15.367
I was no longer needed.

33:16.100 --> 33:18.933
I am so desperately lonely...

33:21.367 --> 33:23.367
I'm ready to scream.

33:26.634 --> 33:28.867
Both of the times you
say you knew yourself

33:28.868 --> 33:30.334
you attribute to a man.

33:31.067 --> 33:34.433
So of course if he betrays
you, you're left adrift.

33:34.434 --> 33:38.666
With luck, we all find
someone who can support us.

33:38.667 --> 33:40.433
But that's not where
we look for strength.

33:40.434 --> 33:41.634
That lies within.

33:43.501 --> 33:46.667
The truth wrapped in
a platitude, I know.

33:49.134 --> 33:52.067
Ask, "Who am I?"

33:52.534 --> 33:55.133
Not in relationship to someone
else but to yourself.

33:55.134 --> 33:57.299
Ask, "What do <i>I</i> want to do?

33:57.300 --> 34:00.133
What is it that will fulfill me?"

34:00.134 --> 34:01.833
What will fulfill you, Olivia?

34:01.834 --> 34:02.933
You.

34:07.601 --> 34:11.400
Pursue that... and
there's your strength.

34:15.768 --> 34:17.100
In here.

34:19.100 --> 34:20.701
To be found.

34:36.933 --> 34:38.533
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

34:38.534 --> 34:41.632
Thank you. And thanks for the scarf.

34:41.634 --> 34:43.299
I'll see to your bike.

34:43.300 --> 34:44.699
Thank you.

34:44.701 --> 34:46.299
It's nearly done.

34:46.300 --> 34:48.632
I want the real Rose back.

34:48.634 --> 34:51.300
Well, maybe this <i>is the real her.</i>

34:51.734 --> 34:53.033
Sorry.

34:53.868 --> 34:56.065
You put her in harm's
way, then you judge her.

34:56.067 --> 34:58.433
I am sorry.

34:58.434 --> 35:00.167
Just do what you have to.

35:06.234 --> 35:09.534
Come on, Rose. Let's
show Carolyn your scarf.

35:13.501 --> 35:16.400
This is a vicious exercise
in character assassination.

35:16.401 --> 35:18.500
And what if I told you it's all true?

35:18.501 --> 35:21.366
You're telling me that Regina
killed the young Davis woman

35:21.367 --> 35:23.400
- in trying to poison Sarah?
- Yes.

35:23.401 --> 35:26.166
- You've said nothing until now?
- We had no proof to offer.

35:26.167 --> 35:27.899
Exactly.

35:27.900 --> 35:30.867
I'm sorry, but... this is monstrous.

35:30.868 --> 35:34.366
And that is exactly why we waited...

35:34.367 --> 35:36.666
to be able to bring you that proof.

35:36.667 --> 35:39.366
George, I know you must
be feeling manipulated

35:39.367 --> 35:40.333
and excluded.

35:40.334 --> 35:41.733
I understand.

35:41.734 --> 35:43.500
But I am begging you.

35:43.501 --> 35:46.299
We have spent months preparing this.

35:46.300 --> 35:49.334
"We" very much includes Sarah.

35:55.367 --> 35:57.700
You'll be turning heads
at the next bush dance.

35:57.701 --> 36:00.099
I should hope so.

36:00.100 --> 36:02.366
Well, you'd best check if you're needed,

36:02.367 --> 36:04.433
and, um, I should find Father.

36:04.434 --> 36:05.633
I'll see you later.

36:05.634 --> 36:08.100
And Mother wants to talk
to you about your book.

36:08.601 --> 36:09.999
Not now.

36:10.000 --> 36:11.366
You've written a book?

36:11.367 --> 36:12.567
It's all right, Rose.

36:14.701 --> 36:17.199
It's in her room if you need it back.

36:17.200 --> 36:18.200
Thank you, Rose.

36:23.000 --> 36:24.400
Not in front of her.

36:24.401 --> 36:26.700
She'd have no idea.

36:26.701 --> 36:29.833
ANNA: The last thing we need
is Regina getting wind of it.

36:29.834 --> 36:33.634
If this doesn't make Father
divorce her, nothing will.

36:37.667 --> 36:40.133
That certainly blew away the cobwebs.

36:40.134 --> 36:41.767
You have quite a seat on you.

36:41.768 --> 36:43.966
- Hm! Cheeky man.
- (CHUCKLES)

36:43.967 --> 36:46.066
I've always found it
wildly suggestive myself.

36:46.067 --> 36:47.834
Ma'am, there's something...

36:49.534 --> 36:51.701
Have to go and check on Lizzie.

36:54.834 --> 36:56.932
Gino was hiding something. I could tell.

36:56.933 --> 36:58.733
But then Anna came back,
so he didn't say.

36:58.734 --> 37:00.633
Whatever it was, he was cross with her.

37:00.634 --> 37:03.233
And then Mrs. Duncan was
talking about some book,

37:03.234 --> 37:04.932
and Anna got real funny,
and I could tell...

37:04.933 --> 37:07.601
Stop! The point, please.

37:08.501 --> 37:11.133
Anna's written a book. Old Mrs.
Bligh's got it.

37:11.134 --> 37:13.033
I think it's to hurt you.

37:15.933 --> 37:18.000
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

38:03.768 --> 38:06.167
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

38:15.967 --> 38:17.567
(GRUNTING)

38:19.401 --> 38:21.967
(CLANKING)

38:34.167 --> 38:36.100
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

38:44.834 --> 38:47.234
Time enough, I think.

38:49.234 --> 38:50.833
Good luck.

38:50.834 --> 38:53.601
Give her curry. Watch the old ticker.

38:59.667 --> 39:01.600
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

39:01.601 --> 39:03.434
(PAGES TURNING)

39:04.434 --> 39:06.267
ELIZABETH: What are you doing in here?

39:06.834 --> 39:08.800
What are you doing with that?

39:08.801 --> 39:11.299
This explains your welcome.

39:11.300 --> 39:12.633
You hypocritical old hag.

39:12.634 --> 39:14.666
You give that to me and get out.

39:14.667 --> 39:17.099
This is what that little
bitch was doing in Italy.

39:17.100 --> 39:18.867
Penning a catalog of lies.

39:18.868 --> 39:20.566
But we both know it's true.

39:20.567 --> 39:22.666
There's not a shred of truth in it.

39:22.667 --> 39:24.501
Then why are you so agitated?

39:25.100 --> 39:27.800
Because that Nordmann
slut used similar tales

39:27.801 --> 39:29.367
to try and see me arrested.

39:30.000 --> 39:32.367
I assume it was her who got in your ear.

39:32.900 --> 39:35.100
You seem scared, Regina.

39:36.200 --> 39:38.234
Disgusted.

39:39.033 --> 39:43.367
It's a filthy... scurrilous... slander.

39:43.933 --> 39:46.633
And I will sue Anna and any
publisher who touches it.

39:46.634 --> 39:48.366
Oh, please do.

39:48.367 --> 39:50.366
Do us the favor.

39:50.367 --> 39:53.567
The stronger your reaction,
the greater the conjecture.

39:54.367 --> 39:56.733
You may have Sergeant
Taylor under the thumb,

39:56.734 --> 39:58.999
but sufficient fuss could
see an investigation

39:59.000 --> 40:01.033
at levels well above his.

40:02.367 --> 40:03.800
And no proof to back it.

40:03.801 --> 40:06.567
But a highly circumstantial case.

40:10.167 --> 40:11.601
Has George seen this?

40:13.100 --> 40:15.700
He will, soon enough.

40:15.701 --> 40:17.366
If he reads this,

40:17.367 --> 40:20.366
if anyone does beyond your
malicious inner cabal,

40:20.367 --> 40:23.601
I will reveal every sordid truth I know.

40:24.434 --> 40:28.466
Your grandson and his sodomite surgeon.

40:28.467 --> 40:33.467
Olivia, the adulterous whore
and George's bastard.

40:33.933 --> 40:36.733
Speaking of which...

40:36.734 --> 40:41.334
infant mortality rates
are such a concern.

40:42.734 --> 40:45.768
If you've killed once,
you can kill again.

40:46.501 --> 40:48.500
So you admit it. (EXHALES DEEPLY)

40:48.501 --> 40:50.334
Hypothetically.

40:51.634 --> 40:54.100
Go on. Take the risk.

40:54.734 --> 40:57.768
Not even you would hurt a child.

40:59.933 --> 41:01.768
The Jew's brat?

41:02.933 --> 41:04.900
With pleasure.

41:06.801 --> 41:09.700
I want every copy of this
in my room within the hour.

41:09.701 --> 41:13.199
And if I learn there are others,
if it ever appears in print,

41:13.200 --> 41:18.734
if George ever knows... I
will destroy the lot of you.

41:22.401 --> 41:25.366
(UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

41:25.367 --> 41:26.666
(DOOR CLOSES)

41:26.667 --> 41:28.567
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

41:48.434 --> 41:50.099
It's ironed, ma'am.

41:50.100 --> 41:51.367
Thank you.

41:52.868 --> 41:54.467
And for your information.

42:05.000 --> 42:08.400
Buy yourself something
next time we're in town.

42:08.401 --> 42:09.801
Ma'am.

42:10.367 --> 42:12.367
You've done very well.

42:14.967 --> 42:17.200
(COINS JINGLING)

42:29.067 --> 42:30.701
George?

42:32.501 --> 42:34.367
We have a tiger by the tail.

42:35.300 --> 42:36.767
You understand why we did...

42:36.768 --> 42:38.467
I do.

42:38.534 --> 42:39.834
I do.

42:40.768 --> 42:43.334
Without proof, I would have doubted you.

42:45.634 --> 42:48.032
There's no point in
involving the local police.

42:48.033 --> 42:50.299
She'd be incarcerated
by now if there were.

42:50.300 --> 42:51.701
Yes. Of course.

42:53.300 --> 42:56.467
Publishing is one road to justice.

42:56.933 --> 42:58.533
But we need something more definitive.

42:58.534 --> 43:00.367
Oh, I agree.

43:04.734 --> 43:06.534
She's played me.

43:07.634 --> 43:10.734
I... need to stare that
truth in the face...

43:13.801 --> 43:16.367
and see her where she belongs.

43:28.967 --> 43:29.966
(GASPS)

43:29.967 --> 43:31.833
Call it a review of
your pedestrian prose!

43:31.834 --> 43:32.767
How dare you!

43:32.768 --> 43:35.567
One word to George, you all suffer.

43:36.134 --> 43:38.867
Your engagement is punishment enough.

43:38.868 --> 43:40.299
Oh, there you are.

43:40.300 --> 43:42.700
I'm popping in to check
on the new hospital wing.

43:42.701 --> 43:44.334
I thought you might like to join me.

43:45.134 --> 43:46.300
I'd love to.

43:47.167 --> 43:49.434
It's uh, it's so good to be home.

43:50.701 --> 43:52.833
Perhaps Elizabeth might like to join us.

43:52.834 --> 43:55.166
I've just asked her. She declined.

43:55.167 --> 43:56.966
Perhaps you could check on her.

43:56.967 --> 43:59.200
She looks a little, uh, piqued.

43:59.933 --> 44:01.200
Shall we?

44:06.367 --> 44:08.634
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

44:12.401 --> 44:13.366
Are you all right?

44:13.367 --> 44:14.899
I'm all right. I'm...

44:14.900 --> 44:16.366
He knows?

44:16.367 --> 44:17.700
He has to.

44:17.701 --> 44:18.800
Doesn't he?

44:18.801 --> 44:20.200
We'll see.

44:20.734 --> 44:23.200
It went to perfection.

44:26.434 --> 44:29.134
It'll be a wonderful
facility when it's done.

44:30.900 --> 44:32.834
How's the budget going?

44:33.567 --> 44:36.099
I'll show you if you have time.

44:36.100 --> 44:37.899
Would you mind waiting?

44:37.900 --> 44:39.767
I'll be outside in the sun.

44:39.768 --> 44:41.366
I won't be a moment.

44:41.367 --> 44:43.634
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

44:55.367 --> 44:58.333
Mother tells me you're aware of this...

44:58.334 --> 45:00.367
this situation.

45:01.134 --> 45:03.834
I've only recently been enlightened.

45:04.367 --> 45:05.367
Ah.

45:05.900 --> 45:07.501
I did wonder.

45:08.601 --> 45:09.634
Why the charade?

45:10.167 --> 45:14.343
She's made threats...
to the entire family.

45:16.434 --> 45:19.733
I need her feeling secure
before I make my move.

45:19.734 --> 45:21.167
What can I do?

45:22.000 --> 45:24.501
I might require your
signature on some documents.

45:25.033 --> 45:26.434
Of course.

45:28.033 --> 45:30.567
If anyone had told me
this morning that this...

45:35.300 --> 45:38.033
Uh, one thing before you go.

45:38.868 --> 45:41.100
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

45:59.234 --> 46:00.833
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

46:00.834 --> 46:05.400
And she's made threats against
both James and Henry.

46:05.401 --> 46:06.800
There's no immediate cause for concern,

46:06.801 --> 46:10.566
but I trust they're not
staying together tonight.

46:10.567 --> 46:12.633
Not to my knowledge.

46:12.634 --> 46:14.366
I knew there was something going on.

46:14.367 --> 46:16.566
Oh, we didn't want you bothered with it.

46:16.567 --> 46:18.634
There's little choice now.

46:19.200 --> 46:20.700
If I may suggest,

46:20.701 --> 46:23.533
perhaps go down to the city in
the morning and locate him.

46:23.534 --> 46:26.299
He should be seen with his wife
in case she spreads her malice.

46:26.300 --> 46:27.334
You're right.

46:28.167 --> 46:30.299
I've made decisions about
my future, anyway,

46:30.300 --> 46:31.900
which I'm keen to share.

46:33.868 --> 46:36.501
Well, you do seem somewhat lighter.

46:37.634 --> 46:38.567
Focused.

46:40.334 --> 46:41.933
James first.

46:42.967 --> 46:44.734
You've had us worried, you know.

46:45.701 --> 46:47.868
I've had myself worried.

46:48.501 --> 46:49.633
No more.

46:49.685 --> 46:51.634
(BABY CRYING)

46:52.701 --> 46:54.734
I'll leave first thing.

46:55.467 --> 46:57.434
It's all right.

46:57.501 --> 46:58.768
It's all right.

46:59.501 --> 47:01.032
It's all right.

47:01.033 --> 47:03.933
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

47:19.534 --> 47:21.433
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

47:21.434 --> 47:23.366
So now things take their course.

47:23.367 --> 47:26.033
It's hard to believe it's nearly over.

47:26.834 --> 47:29.032
I'd love to know George's intentions.

47:29.033 --> 47:31.666
But the less we know, the less
likely we'll tip his hand.

47:31.667 --> 47:33.299
I suspect that's his thinking.

47:33.300 --> 47:34.334
Mm.

47:34.868 --> 47:37.734
(SHEEP BLEATING, CHICKENS CLUCKING)

47:43.868 --> 47:45.834
(ENGINE STARTS)

47:51.834 --> 47:53.033
Well?

47:53.534 --> 47:57.300
It's done, but, um, things
have to stay as they are.

47:58.300 --> 48:00.600
And George, uh, he believes it?
He accepts it all?

48:00.601 --> 48:02.800
But Regina can't know he does.

48:02.801 --> 48:04.366
He's got some plan for her.

48:04.367 --> 48:06.099
Sees her behind bars.

48:06.100 --> 48:07.367
And Rose?

48:07.801 --> 48:09.633
Just a little bit longer.

48:09.634 --> 48:11.932
- (SPEAKING ITALIAN)
- What?

48:11.933 --> 48:13.600
- No. I've had it.
- Gino.

48:13.601 --> 48:15.032
It's always something, Anna.

48:15.033 --> 48:16.932
Some plot, some scheme, some lie.

48:16.933 --> 48:18.166
Use Rose. Who cares?

48:18.167 --> 48:20.633
A-A baby dies. Y-You buy a new one.

48:20.634 --> 48:22.199
Someone's poisoned. Forget the cops.

48:22.200 --> 48:24.366
Let's do it ourselves.
Your family is sick!

48:24.367 --> 48:26.633
- It's all so we...
- No, no, no! I don't care!

48:26.634 --> 48:28.099
Now you can't even give me a son!

48:28.100 --> 48:29.534
What's the point?!

48:30.634 --> 48:32.567
You don't mean that.

48:37.033 --> 48:38.367
Yeah.

48:40.167 --> 48:41.134
I do.

48:44.100 --> 48:45.501
What is the point?

48:53.000 --> 48:56.200
(DOOR OPENS)

49:01.701 --> 49:02.700
Oh.

49:02.701 --> 49:04.966
I thought Mrs. Bligh was back.

49:04.967 --> 49:08.434
You should be out on your
ear with no reference.

49:08.900 --> 49:10.700
What have I done?

49:10.701 --> 49:12.867
The picture of innocence.

49:12.868 --> 49:17.167
If you can't resist your nature,
the truth is there, to be read.

49:38.634 --> 49:39.932
Where did you get that?

49:39.933 --> 49:41.899
Uh, old Mrs. Bligh just dropped them in.

49:41.900 --> 49:44.233
- Just?
- Uh, only just.

49:44.234 --> 49:45.500
How much have you read?

49:45.501 --> 49:46.834
A few words.

49:48.768 --> 49:50.033
Good.

49:50.534 --> 49:54.234
"House of Lies." The title says it all.

49:55.601 --> 49:59.533
You're the one person I
can trust, my darling.

49:59.534 --> 50:01.700
And Mr. Bligh.

50:01.701 --> 50:03.433
Of course.

50:03.434 --> 50:06.366
That old woman was so horrible to me.

50:06.367 --> 50:10.133
Oh, and then I was mean.

50:10.134 --> 50:12.234
I'm sorry.

50:13.200 --> 50:16.134
(SIGHS) You've been such a support.

50:21.033 --> 50:23.768
There's only one thing
these are good for.

50:31.734 --> 50:33.834
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

51:21.701 --> 51:23.434
So it's done?

51:26.567 --> 51:27.567
It is.

51:28.334 --> 51:29.933
And now justice.

51:31.768 --> 51:34.300
In a way that sees us all safe.

51:39.768 --> 51:41.434
Hello, David.

51:44.167 --> 51:45.967
Jack showed you.

51:51.868 --> 51:53.734
David Bligh.

51:57.300 --> 51:59.768
How could I love you and deny you that?

52:03.567 --> 52:06.434
(DOWN-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS)

